Revision history for Algorithm-Classifier-IsolationForest

0.3.0   2026-07-01
        - fit() can now handle training data with missing (undef) feature
          cells, selectable via the new `missing =>` constructor option:
            die    :: croak on undef in the training data (default)
            zero   :: treat a missing cell as the value 0
            impute :: fill with the per-feature mean/median (see `impute_with`)
            nan    :: range over present values and route missing rows to the
                      right child, consistently at fit and score time
        - new `impute_with => 'mean'|'median'` option for impute mode
        - missing strategy + impute fill vector are persisted in saved models;
          models from older releases load as `zero` (the prior undef -> 0
          scoring behaviour)
        - new `use_openmp_fit` constructor option: builds fit()'s trees across
          OpenMP threads within a single process using a thread-private
          splitmix64 PRNG per tree; reproducible for a fixed seed + n_trees
          regardless of OMP_NUM_THREADS, but NOT bit-identical to the
          pure-Perl / serial-C paths (documented trade-off: thread-safety
          requires a separate PRNG, unlike use_c which uses Drand01())
        - serial C fit builder (build_forest_xs) is now bit-identical to the
          pure-Perl fit path for the same seed, in both axis and extended mode
          and across all missing strategies; switching use_c on/off never
          changes the model, only how fast it is built
        - pack_input_xs extended with miss_mode / fill_sv so the C input
          packer handles all four missing strategies (zero, impute, nan)
          rather than hard-coding 0.0 for undef cells
        - parallel_fit and use_openmp_fit do not compose: forked children
          never start their own OpenMP region to avoid a fork()+libgomp hang;
          setting both just means parallel_fit wins
        - new impute_fill_xs C helper computes the per-feature mean/median
          impute fill vector in C when the backend is available
        - the C build is now tunable via environment variables read at first
          module load: IF_ARCH=<value> adds -march=<value>, IF_NATIVE=1 is
          shorthand for IF_ARCH=native, IF_OPT overrides the default -O3,
          and IF_NO_C=1 skips building the C backend entirely; values are
          validated (bad ones warn and fall back to the defaults) and the
          flags actually used are exposed via $OPT_LEVEL
        - new POD sections on tuning the C build and the OpenMP runtime
          (OMP_NUM_THREADS, OMP_PROC_BIND/OMP_PLACES)
        - `accel` CLI command now documents the IF_* build tuning variables
          and prints the build flags in use when the C backend is active
        - Tests: t/34-missing-values.t covering all four strategies, the
          C/pure-Perl agreement under nan mode, and persistence round-trips
        - Tests: t/03-fit-determinism.t verifying reproducibility across all
          backends (pure Perl, serial C, OpenMP-parallel C) and confirming
          the parallel_fit + use_openmp_fit safety behaviour
        - Tests: t/04-accel-tuning.t covering the IF_* build tuning
          variables, including that invalid IF_OPT/IF_ARCH values are
          rejected rather than passed to the compiler command line
        - Tests: update various ones to test against both C and pure Perl
        - Benchmarking: bench-sklearn-scoring.pl now compares pure Perl, C,
          and C+OpenMP fit/score paths against sklearn side by side
        - fix: calling fit() a second time on an already-fitted model with
          contamination set no longer learns the threshold against the
          previous fit's packed scoring buffers (bug present since 0.2.0)
        - minor POD fixes (wrong method names in the path_lengths /
          score_samples / score_predict_samples examples, missing package
          name in the extended-mode SYNOPSIS example, assorted typos)

0.2.1   2026-06-30/14:30
        - derp... actually update MANIFEST so a bunch of files from last release
          are actually included

0.2.0   2026-06-30/14:15
        - C acceleration via Inline::C for core fit and predict ops
        - OpenMP support for parallel multi-threaded fitting and predict ops
        - SIMD (AVX/SSE) acceleration where available
        - Data packing support for compact model storage (new `pack` CLI command)
        - Parallel fit capability
        - New `score_predict_split` method
        - New `accel` CLI command for querying available acceleration flags
        - New `bench` CLI command for running built-in benchmarks
        - New `info` CLI command with expanded model introspection
        - Benchmarking scripts covering fit, predict, scoring, and accel modes
        - Tests: accel flag detection, accel selection, undef column handling,
          data packing, parallel fit, sklearn comparison (including undef),
          and CLI
        - minor tweaks to `csv2plot` for a bit nicer rendering
        - minor POD fixes

0.1.0   2026-06-23/03:15
        - add csv2plot helper command for graphing

0.0.1   2026-06-21/21:45
        - initial release
